Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for the violation of the time and order of payment of goods (works, services) when making purchases for state and municipal needs.
This law is designed to address the very acute problem of non-compliance with its obligations by customers in the execution of public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation, when entrepreneurs could not receive payment for already executed state and municipal contracts, was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia ordered the Attorney General of the Russian Federation to take the problem on special control.
Because the businessmen themselves were unable to cope with unfaithful customers who entered into unfunded contracts, they tried to evade payment obligations and included illegal terms in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public contracts by the prosecutor's office submitted 9.7 thousand submissions, according to the results of their examination, 4.5 thousand officials submitted to disciplinary responsibility, in administrative cases - 533, from prosecution to prosecution bodies of 46
As a result, the debt to entrepreneurs amounted to more than 66 billion rubles.
And these huge sums were accumulated by far not as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs have resulted in more modest amounts.
Here's a typical case.
The head of a small company won a competition for the provision of social transport services for several million rubles.
The man invested all his turnover funds, fully fulfilled the obligations, but the money put in the time did not receive.
The result is a growing financial comma of debts on wages, taxes, loans, which would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not seek help from the prosecutor’s office.
In a number of regions, the problem has now been maximized.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt under state and municipal contracts, identified by prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt ratios continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor ' s office operates in the manual anti-crisis management mode.
The Prosecutor-General personally holds travel meetings with local authorities, in which they are subjectively aware of all violations committed by the prosecutors and the measures taken to remedy them immediately.
Such operational meetings have already taken place this year in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
Qualitatively improve the payment discipline of public contractors will be able to implement the Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendment to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in relation to the determination of the liability of the public contractor, and the burden of administrative liability of the client for the breach.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Prosecutor General’s Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences article, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand to 50 thousand rubles for violation by the official of the customer of the term and order of payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
And if an official has already been subject to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he is expected to be disqualified for a period of one year to two years.
All prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
