The governor’s subordinates called the claim void, and the comment on the internet was written in the spirit of “well what”.
“It’s just Facebook,” many will say.
But it's also important.
And this is especially important when it comes to a guy like Hogan.
He is an astoundingly popular Republican governor in a democratic predominantly state.
He is second in the approval rating among the 50 governors of the country.
Hogan is not a reluctant reactionary.
He has demonstrated a firm hand in the governance of the state and a commitment to its principles.
He also happily uses Facebook as the primary way of communicating with his voters and with jokes demonstrating on his page his laziness after chemotherapy.
