Most likely, it could also be a scam.
To make a solemn oath those wishing to obtain Russian citizenship will be after officials check their documents.
But the Russian passport a person will only receive after he has made a vow, follows from the refined text.
A week ago in the draft it was said that the oath should precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text says that Russia will be sworn in from the age of 18, not from the age of 14.
The rule remains that those who are not able or are limited in their ability to act will be exempted from the oath, as well as those who are unable to pronounce, read or sign the oath text themselves.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to exempt from this procedure and "other persons",
Also in the updated bill is prescribed a special procedure for admission to the Russian citizens of the residents of Ukraine, who are considered to be carriers of the Russian language.
