We've been thinking about how to help the crew.
At that time, a contact group of military experts, representatives of the State Duma was established, our work was supported by the head of Chechnya Ramzan Kadyrov.
And how did it turn out that you led her?
Since I have been working in Libya since 2008, I have been asked to lead the group.
Our activity was not limited to the release of the sailors from "Mechanics of Chebotarev".
We managed to establish contacts with representatives of all major groups confronting each other in the Libyan conflict - and from Tripoli (where the UN-recognized government headed by Faiz Sarajevo is based. - "I", "I"), and with the "Haleuk" (residence of the parliament, which is based on the United Nations-led government led by Faiz Sarajevo.
Thanks to the active participation of Ahmed Metig (Vice Prime Minister of Libya - "I"), we were able to quickly agree on the release of Russian sailors.
Then it was decided to use these contacts more effectively, to create a contact group.
Its task is to analyze the situation, identify key factors and players, dialogue with all parties to the conflict.
I would like to emphasize in particular: in Libya we do not want to associate with any of the parties to the conflict, we are conducting a dialogue with everyone.
How many people are in the contact group and how many of them are permanently in Libya?
There are now five people in the contact group.
Among them are people who have experience working in force structures, including the Ministry of Defence.
We also want to include a group of specialists in the region, representatives of the Institute of the Middle East RAN.
None of our staff is permanently in Libya, and that is not necessary yet.
Are there Russian military advisers, instructors in Libya now?
