There are no Russian military specialists in Libya.
All conversations and publications about this do not correspond to reality.
But in your contact group, ex-military members are...
Yes, and their presence is necessary.
For example, when we visit hot spots.
Or such cities closed to a certain point for us, such as Misurata (where militia units are based, which played a role in the overthrow of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011 and have significantly increased in subsequent years).
We arrived in Missouri in January of this year.
