“Life with a person who has been with me since I was born is a pain that will remain with me for the rest of my life,” she said.
This case is likely to be a legal precedent, as there is no law in Massachusetts that would provide for the responsibility for the advice of a person to commit suicide.
In 2014, when Roy was found dead in a car with symptoms of carbon dioxide poisoning, Carter was 17 years old.
